---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Fenn Agritech"
  description="How this site handles data."
  currentPage="privacy"
>
  <section class="legal">
    <div class="legal__inner">
      <p class="legal__label">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="legal__title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="legal__meta">Last updated: 17 May 2026</p>

      <p class="legal__intro">This website (fenn.wichman.io) is an independent GRC portfolio project. Fenn Agritech is a fictional company depicted on this site and is not a legal entity. The website is operated by Drea Wichman, an individual based in London, United Kingdom. Drea Wichman is the data controller for any personal data collected through this site, and can be contacted at <a href="mailto:privacy@wichman.io" class="legal__link">privacy@wichman.io</a>. This site aims to comply with the UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>

      <h2 class="legal__h2">Personal data this site collects</h2>
      <p class="legal__p">This site is a static website hosted on GitHub Pages. It does not use cookies, analytics, advertising scripts, or tracking technologies. Providing personal data is not required to use this site. The following limited personal data may be processed:</p>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>Server logs.</strong> When you visit, GitHub Pages automatically records your IP address and basic request metadata (browser type, referring URL, timestamp) for security and abuse-prevention purposes. The site owner does not access, retain, or use these logs. See GitHub's Privacy Statement for how GitHub processes this data.</p>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>Voluntary contact.</strong> If you choose to email, message, or otherwise contact the site owner using the links provided (email, LinkedIn, GitHub), your contact information and the contents of your message will be received and stored in the relevant inbox or platform.</p>

      <h2 class="legal__h2">Purpose and legal basis</h2>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>Server logs:</strong> processed by GitHub Pages for security, fraud prevention, and abuse protection of the hosting infrastructure. Legal basis: legitimate interest under Article 6(1)(f) UK GDPR in operating a secure website.</p>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>Voluntary contact:</strong> processed by the site owner solely to read your message and respond to it. Legal basis: legitimate interest under Article 6(1)(f) UK GDPR in receiving and responding to correspondence you have chosen to send.</p>

      <h2 class="legal__h2">Who this data is shared with</h2>
      <p class="legal__p">The site owner does not share personal data with any third parties for marketing or any other purpose. The only parties that may process personal data in connection with this site are:</p>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>GitHub, Inc.</strong> (hosting provider, based in the United States), which processes server logs as described above.</p>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>Proton AG</strong> (Switzerland), which provides the email inbox used to receive messages sent to addresses on this site.</p>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>LinkedIn and GitHub</strong> if you choose to contact the site owner through those platforms, in which case those services process your message according to their own privacy policies.</p>

      <h2 class="legal__h2">International data transfers</h2>
      <p class="legal__p">GitHub, Inc. is based in the United States. Transfers rely on appropriate safeguards including GitHub's contractual commitments under the UK Addendum to the EU Standard Contractual Clauses. Email is processed in Switzerland by Proton AG. Switzerland is recognised by the UK as providing an adequate level of data protection.</p>

      <h2 class="legal__h2">How long data is retained</h2>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>Server logs:</strong> retained by GitHub Pages according to GitHub's data retention policy.</p>
      <p class="legal__p"><strong>Voluntary contact:</strong> retained by the site owner only as long as needed to respond to your message, generally no longer than 24 months, after which messages are deleted unless there is an ongoing reason to keep them.</p>

      <h2 class="legal__h2">Your rights</h2>
      <p class="legal__p">If your personal data is processed in connection with this site, you have the right to request access to your data, request that it be corrected or deleted, object to or restrict its processing, and (where applicable) request that it be provided to you in a portable format.</p>
      <p class="legal__p">To exercise any of these rights, or to make a complaint, email <a href="mailto:privacy@wichman.io" class="legal__link">privacy@wichman.io</a>. Complaints will be acknowledged and responded to without undue delay.</p>
      <p class="legal__p">You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (<a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="legal__link">ico.org.uk</a>), the UK supervisory authority for data protection.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    background: var(--color-light);
    padding: 80px 0 120px;
  }
  .legal__inner {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--gutter);
  }
  .legal__label {
    color: var(--color-emerald);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .legal__title {
    font-size: 44px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -1.5px;
    color: var(--text-on-light);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal__meta {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-muted-on-light);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .legal__intro {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-on-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .legal__h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-on-light);
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal__p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-on-light);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal__p strong {
    color: var(--text-on-light);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .legal__link {
    color: var(--color-emerald);
  }
  .legal__link:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .legal__title { font-size: 32px; }
    .legal { padding: 48px 0 80px; }
  }
</style>